<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001p=
t;
text-indent:-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>(b)=
<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Truck drivers are not covered in the following
instances:</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001p=
t;
line-height:normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin=
-bottom:
0in;margin-left:1.0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>(1)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Time=
s New Roman"'>&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Material delivery truck driv=
ers
while off “the site of the work.”</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin=
-bottom:
0in;margin-left:1.0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal'><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin=
-bottom:
0in;margin-left:1.0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>(2)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Time=
s New Roman"'>&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Drivers of a contractor or
subcontractor traveling between a Davis-Bacon job and a commercial supply
facility while they are off the “site of the work.”</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115=
%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin=
-bottom:
0in;margin-left:1.0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>(3)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Time=
s New Roman"'>&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Truck drivers whose time spe=
nt on
the site of the work is de minimis, such as only a few minutes at a time me=
rely
to pick up or drop off materials or supplies. </span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-=
height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-=
height:
normal'><b><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>15e23 - Tugboat operators,
tugmasters, captains and deckhands.</span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-=
height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001p=
t;
line-height:normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>In general, tugboat
personnel are engaged in navigational transportation, and are not considere=
d to
be laborers or mechanics. However, for example, if a crew member on a dredg=
ing
project is performing work directly related to the covered construction pro=
ject
such as connecting, extending, and controlling the pipeline through which
dredged material is being pumped, the individual would be considered a labo=
rer
or mechanic for the time so spent and entitled to the applicable prevailing
wage rate. (Also see FOH 15j00.)</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-=
height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-=
height:
normal'><b><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>15e24 - Volunteers.</span></b><=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-=
height:
normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001p=
t;
line-height:normal'><span style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>There are no exception=
s to
DBRA coverage for volunteer labor unless an exception is specifically provi=
ded
for in the particular D-B Related Act under which the project funds are
derived. Furthermore, DOL does not have the authority to grant waivers for
volunteer labor. (See FOH 15c00.)</span></p>

