shortfall in profits which results in actual payments to the pension plan b=
eing
less than the rate at which the contractor claimed DBRA credit throughout t=
he
year would have to be made up by the contractor when the account is settled=
 at
year end, by paying the difference (shortfall) in cash directly to the
