provisions provide that forfeitures are to be used to reduce a contractor’s
future contributions or are allocated to the remaining employees’ accounts.=
 In
either case, such provisions are not prohibited under the Davis-Bacon Act.
However, the contractor may not use such forfeitures as a credit toward mee=
ting
