employer shall not employ any employee to work in excess of 40 hours in a
workweek unless such employee receives compensation for his or her employme=
nt
in excess of the hours above specified at a rate not less than one and one-=
half
times the regular rate at which he or she is employed. (29 CFR § 778.101.)<=
/span></p>

